This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on using state-of-the-art CNN architectures to classify art styles and visualize the characteristic parts of paintings. Additionally, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it explores the use of machines to automate and scale the task of identifying and understanding art styles. The paper also discusses network analysis, which may fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category, and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it aims to discover new linkages among different art styles and artists.
